3) Map schema directly to your UI screens
Auth
Sign up / Sign in

auth.users, then create row in public.profiles

Customer flow
Home

customer identity: profiles

active jobs: jobs where customer_id = auth.uid()

notifications: notifications where user_id = auth.uid()

Explore (map + list)

mechanic card core: public.profiles (mechanic name/photo) + mechanics + mechanic_profiles

map point: mechanic_locations.location

badges: mechanic_skills → skills, mechanic_tools → tools, mechanic_safety → safety_measures

trust: mechanic_confidence_score(mechanic_id)

Mechanic detail (customer view)

profiles, mechanics, mechanic_profiles, mechanic_locations

join tables to show checklist groups

Create job

jobs insert with customer_id = auth.uid()

optionally vehicle_id from vehicles

Quotes

customer reads: quote_requests where customer_id = auth.uid()

Job progress

jobs (status/accepted_mechanic_id)

messages where job_id = …

Mechanic flow
Mechanic onboarding

mechanics (onboarding_completed, is_available, etc.)

mechanic_profiles (shop_name/bio/radius)

mechanic_locations (location)

checklist writes: mechanic_skills, mechanic_tools, mechanic_safety

schedule: mechanic_availability

Leads / jobs

mechanic reads jobs (searching) + gets assigned via quote_requests

once accepted: jobs.accepted_mechanic_id = auth.uid()

Inbox

messages where sender is mechanic OR job is assigned to mechanic


